# Teardown / Analysis Thread Template

## Tweet 1 (Hook)
{Bold claim or surprising insight from the teardown. Lead with your most interesting finding, not the thing you're analyzing.}

I broke down {thing being analyzed}. Here's what I found:

## Tweet 2 (What We're Analyzing)
{Introduce the subject: product, company, codebase, strategy, etc. Brief context: why it's worth analyzing.}

## Tweet 3-N (Breakdown Points)
{Number}. {Finding or observation title}

{2-3 sentences explaining what you found, why it matters, and what the reader should notice.}

{Include specifics: screenshots, data, code snippets, comparisons.}

<!-- Repeat for each finding. Aim for 4-7 breakdown points. -->
<!-- Each tweet should deliver a standalone insight. -->

## Tweet N+1 (Synthesis)
The pattern across all of this:

{1-2 sentences connecting the findings into a larger insight. This is the meta-takeaway.}

## Final Tweet (CTA)
{What should the reader do with this analysis? Apply it to their own work? Look at a related example? Share their own teardown?}

{Optional: link to a longer writeup or related resource.}
